JOHANNESBURG - A book is a gift that keeps on giving.  After a year of some heavy-hitting political books, like Jaques Pauw's The President's Keepers and Redi Thlabi's Khwezi: The Remarkable Story of Fezekile Ntsukela Kuzwayo, it is time to relax with some lighter material.  And, amid revelations about the shocking literacy levels among children in South Africa, it's more important than ever to get children reading as well. Watch as eNCA's Andrea van Wyk gives some suggestions of what you can put under the Christmas tree.  eNCA